#Text=NASA 's InSight lander and MarCO craft launch in new mission to Mars
#Text=Monday , May 7 , 2018
#Text=The foggy launch of the Atlas V rocket carrying InSight and the MarCO cubesats .
#Text=Image : Bill Ingalls , NASA .
#Text=On Saturday , United Launch Alliance launched a Atlas V 401 rocket carrying NASA ' s InSight Mars lander and two Mars Cube One ( MarCO ) miniature spacecraft known as cubesats .
#Text=The pre-dawn launch from Vandenberg Air Force Base Space Launch Complex 3E in Lompoc , California was declared a success .
#Text=This was the very first deep space launch from the west coast of the United States , and aimed to send a lander to the surface of the planet Mars to study its interior .

#Text=Launched alongside InSight were two MarCO cubesats , the first to be sent beyond Earth , nicknamed ' WALL-E ' and ' Eve ' after the protagonists of the 2008 animated science fiction film WALL-E .
#Text=They were designed as a dual telecommunications relay for InSight during the spacecraft 's descent through the Martian atmosphere .
#Text=Traditionally , NASA launched interplanetary spacecraft at Cape Canaveral Air Force Station in Florida on the United States ' east coast .
#Text=There , rockets were sent eastward over the Atlantic Ocean , borrowing the Earth 's rotational velocity to shoot their payloads out into the solar system .
#Text=Due to congestion on the launch calendar at Canaveral , NASA chose to launch the spacecraft from from Vandenberg Air Force Base on the country 's west coast instead .
#Text=A launch eastward from Vandenberg would have been dangerous due to densely populated areas being located downrange .
#Text=Instead , rockets launched from Vandenberg were sent in a south-southeast trajectory .
#Text=For Insight and MarCO , the spacecraft was placed in a temporary polar orbit after the launch , with the pair being shot towards Mars during a escape burn performed over the North Pole .
#Text=Despite a heavy fog settling in at the rocket 's launch pad in Lompoc , the United Launch Alliance declared a " 100 % chance of favorable weather for liftoff " .

#Text=Spectators in Lompoc were treated to a mostly obscured view of the launch , though they were witness nonetheless to the sound and shock waves of the Atlas V 's Common Core first stage as it lifted the spacecraft off the ground on-schedule at 4:05 PDT ( 1105 UTC ) .

#Text=People along the coast of southern California and northern Baja California , however , were in clear view of the Atlas V 's main engine burn and the first burn of the rocket 's Centaur upper stage .
#Text=People in Orange County , California were treated to the sight of InSight and the Centaur almost eclipsing the planet Jupiter in the night sky .
#Text=Artist concept of InSight probing the Mars surface Image : NASA / JPL .

#Text=The recently-inaugurated Administrator of NASA , Jim Bridenstine , congratulated the InSight team in an address televised live on NASA TV after the launch , along with the United Launch Alliance on what was their 128th successful launch in a row .
#Text=The InSight mission part of NASA 's Discovery program , a class of low-cost solar system exploration missions .
#Text=It was selected to launch in the program after beating the Comet Hopper and Titan Mare Explorer proposals amongst responses to a 2010 request .
#Text=Both InSight and the MarCO cubesats are en route to Mars .
#Text=InSight
#Text=carries eight scientific instruments , including a seismometer known as Seismic Experiment for Interior Structure ( SEIS ) .
#Text=The SEIS instrument will be recording the very first seismic measurements of Mars , which scientists hope will shed light on the structure of Mars beneath its surface .

#Text=The lander was equipped with two cameras , based on the architecture of the Mars Exploration Rover ' s navigation camera and hazard avoidance camera , to allow mission scientists to monitor the activity of the instruments .
#Text=NASA scheduled a November 26 landing for InSight on a broad plain in the planet 's northern hemisphere , known as Elysium Planitia .
